ium - Daily increases.jpg|thumb|centre|500 px|Graph of the number of daily increase of confirmed cases, hospitalisations, intensive care cases and deaths in Belgium as of 2020-04-30]]\n{{col-end}}\n{{clear}}\n[[File:20200421 B 7948 293 E 14865 125.png|thumb|centre|500 px|[[Logistic function|Logistic growth model]] fits for hospitalised COVID-19 cases in Belgium for data from 15/03/2020 until 21/04/2020. We can make out two phases separated by the yellow horizontal line. One from 15/03/2020 until 31/03/2020 (with a fit in green) and the one form 01/04/2020 until 21/04/2020 (with a fit in blue).\n\nThe initial phase (green) had exponential growth/decline rate of 29.3% The second phase (blue) has much slower exponential growth/decline rate of 12.5% The total number of cumulated hospitalised cases stabilises at 14865.\nBeyond the 21st of April the curves shown are only a trend according to the logistic growth model, these have an uncertainty range associated to them and should not be seen as a prediction.]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[COVID-19 pandemic in France]] \n*[[COVID-19 pandemic in the Netherlands]]\n\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Belgium|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=\"nb\"}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.info-coronavirus.be/en/ www.info-coronavirus.be], information website from the Belgian government\n* [https://epidemio.wiv-isp.be/ID/Pages/2019-nCoV.aspx New Coronavirus (Disease: COVID-19, Virus: SARS-CoV-2)], epidemiological updates in Belgium - [[Sciensano]]\n* [https://epistat.wiv-isp.be/Covid/ EPISTAT- Infectious Diseases Data Explorations & Visualizations], raw data of the pandemic in Belgium  - [[Sciensano]]\n\n{{2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{#related:Sophie Wilm\u00e8s}}\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Netherlands}}\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in France}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belgium| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country|Belgium]]\n